`Random_seed(a)` is returning the size of the seed array, which is typically 8 elements, into the scalar integer a.
The seed array size is typically 8 elements because Fortran's random number generator often uses a seed with a fixed length of 8 integers to ensure sufficient randomness and repeatability in generating sequences of random numbers. This size is determined by the implementation of the random number generator in the Fortran compiler.
